## Python Standards

- **Python 3.11+** (3.12 preferred — see `pyproject.toml`)
- **Type hints — new union syntax only:**
  - ✅ `str | None`, `dict[str, Any]`, `list[str]`, `tuple[int, ...]`
  - ❌ `Optional[str]`, `Dict[str, Any]`, `List[str]`, `Tuple[int, ...]`
- **Ruff** formatter and linter — line length **100**, strict mode
- **Google-style docstrings** on all public functions, classes, and methods
- **Pyright basic mode** for type checking (`uvx pyright ttadev/`)
- **Conventional Commits:** `feat:`, `fix:`, `docs:`, `refactor:`, `test:`, `chore:`

